MGM China Holdings Ltd., the Macau
venture between  Pansy Ho  and the biggest casino operator on the
 Las Vegas Strip , rose on its first trading day in  Hong Kong 
after raising $1.5 billion in an initial public offering.  MGM China gained as much as 6 percent to HK$16.26 in early
Hong Kong trading after selling stock to investors in the IPO
for HK$15.34, the maximum it had sought.  To contact the reporter on this story:
